title: Alpha Particle Bombardments of Natural Nickel Target For the Production of Cu-61

x4freetext: Alpha Particle Bombardments of Natural Nickel Target
For the Production of Cu-61
Department of Chemistry

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Applied Radiation and Isotopes, Vol.29, p.611 (1978)

x4freetext: . Institute of Physical and Chemical
Research Cyclotron. Alpha Particles of 40 MeV and
0.5 to 1 Microampere were Used.
Self-Supporting Foils of Natural Nickel, Thickness
13 - 25 Mg/Cm**2, Prepared by Electroplating on
Cu-Foils. 10 to 13 Foils were Stacked Together Without
Any Other Energy Degrader Being Inserted.
Energy Degradation was Calculated According to
C.F.Williamson Et Al., Cea-R3042(1966).
Information About the Error of the Cross Sections is
Missing. It was Solely Stated That the Uniformity of
The Ni-Foils was Better Than 3% and That the Accuracy
Of the Energy May be not Better Than +-0.5% For
Energies Below 15 MeV.
By Kachapag.
Lakw
Last checking has been done.
Thick Target Yields were Obtained by Summing the
Observed Activities in Each Target Foil.
Since No Formation Cross Section For Zn-61 Could be
Measured Due to Its Short Half-Life, Its Contribution
Was Estimated to be Less Than 1% Using Data of
J.B.Cumming, Phys.Rev.114,1600(1959).
Since the Tty-Curve in the Paper did not Show Single
Data Points, the Values Quoted in the Data Section
Below were Read Off at Arbitrary Energies (COMMENT BY
THE COMPILER OF KACHAPAG).
